imators specifically designed for\ngalaxies at z $>$ 4, to guide interpretations of future, high-redshift\nspectroscopic surveys. We further demonstrate that applying classical z = 0\ncalibrations to high-redshift galaxies can bias O-abundance estimates downward\nby up to 1 dex, leading to the conclusion of a stronger evolution of the\nmass-metallicity relation than the actual one.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 May 2023 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-09"}
